The root cause: in `ModelBase.__new__`, the loop collecting parent links indexed `parent_links` by the related model, so when a model had multiple `OneToOneField`s pointing to the same parent, the *last-declared* one overwrote the actual parent link. A non-`parent_link` field (`origin`/`some_unrelated_document`) could thus get treated as the parent link, while the real one triggered the "Add parent_link=True" error — and the behavior depended on declaration order.

