The root cause: in `alter_index_together`, deleting an index calls `_delete_composed_index` with `{'index': True}`. When a `unique_together` exists on the same fields, the unique constraint is also an index (in most databases), so `_constraint_names` matched both the `_uniq` and `_idx` constraints — yielding 2 results and triggering the `ValueError`.

By passing `{'index': True, 'unique': False}`, the lookup now excludes the unique constraint (which has `unique=True`) and matches only the plain index. The reverse path (`alter_unique_together` with `{'unique': True}`) was already unambiguous since plain indexes have `unique=False`. The MySQL override forwards `*args` to `super()`, so it inherits the fix automatically.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"3669b785-d3de-42fa-abcd-6dd84feda009","total_cost_usd":0.2476945,"usage":{"input_tokens":3010,"cache_creation_input_tokens":10338,"cache_read_input_tokens":164883,"output_tokens":1826,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":10338,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":438,"cache_read_input_tokens":26836,"cache_creation_input_tokens":644,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":644},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":1068,"outputTokens":21,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.001173,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-opus-4-8[1m]":{"inputTokens":3010,"outputTokens":1826,"cacheReadInputTokens":164883,"cacheCreationInputTokens":10338,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.2465215,"contextWindow":1000000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"bdda4455-e363-41df-b824-cb03de232346"}

